lso considers the participation of Bullinger, Pellikan, and Melanchthon in an Erasmian exegetical milieu, it is a case study in the complicated cross-confessional exchange of ideas in the sixteenth century. Kirk Essary examines assumptions about the very nature of theology in the sixteenth century, how it was understood by leading humanist reformers, and how ideas about philosophy and rhetoric were received, appropriated, and shared in a complex intellectual and religious context.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aChristian philosophyxHistoryy16th century. 0aTheologyxHistoryy16th century. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2017z9783110548259oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Pilot 2017z978311066594940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751414340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487514143423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487514143.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066594-9  UTP eBook-Package Pilot 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017